					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of kabbalistic works.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="104v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳovets be-ḳabalah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">קובץ בקבלה</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="2r" to="61v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Hatḥalat ha-ḥokhmah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">התחלת החכמה</title>
							<note>
								<p>Anonymous, by one of the students of Isaac Luria ha-Ar"i.</p>
								<p>See further <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">305-307</ref>, vol. 1.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. MS JTS New York no. 1585, MS Mantua Hebr. 115 and <ref target="Steinschneider_1879" type="number">1795</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥaye ha-῾olam ha-ba</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">חיי עולם הבא</title>
							<locus from="62r" to="97v"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/79054878">Abulafia, Abraham ben Samuel, 1240-1292</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/79054878">אבולעפיה, אברהם בן שמואל</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>See <ref target="Idel_1976" type="page">62-65</ref>.</p>
								<p>The spaces for ῾igulim in the last few pages have not been filled in. Folios 93v-97v contain some short passages from the Zohar and comments on Tiḳunim.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. Or 4596/II (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">757</ref>) and Harley MS 1204/II (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">758</ref>).</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tiḳune shabat</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תקוני שבת</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/38901588">Abraham ben Eliezer, ha-Levi, Berukhim, 1515-1593</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/38901588">אברהם הלוי הזקן</persName>
							</author>
							<locus from="98r" to="104v"/>
							<note>
								<p>A tract by Abraham ha-Levi, called ha-Zaken, on the laws and customs to be observed on the Sabbath. It agrees substantially with an abridgement by Jacob ben Mordecai Poggetto of Reshit ḥokhmah of Elijah da Vidas. Followed by a response on the Ten Commandments, signed by Menahem Azariah da Fano (folio 103r), and a small fragment of Perush ha-tefilot by Joseph ibn Sheraga (folio 104r).</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. Add MS 27014/I (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">792</ref>) and Add MS 26934/V (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">793</ref>).</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
